Feline enteric coronavirus enteritis Feline enteric coronavirus is responsible for an infection of the mature gastrointestinal epithelial cells (see also enterocytes, brush border, microvilli, villi). This intestinal infection has few outward signs, and is usually chronic. The virus may produce a more severe enteritis in young specific-pathogen- kittens.
